08/11/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Seven people have drowned after their boat sank off the Turkish coast near Bodrum, local media reported on Friday (November 6th). Five of the victims were children. The vessel was carrying illegal Afghan immigrants and two Turkish smugglers. One of the Turks died, the other is believed to have escaped. Bad weather conditions, as well as the boat being overloaded, allegedly caused the accident, which happened late Thursday. Thirteen illegal immigrants were rescued by coastguard and fishing boats. (AFP, Xinhua, Anadolu news agency - 06/11/09) 
